# Paper sync rule

When you change **implementation** in this repo, also update [`paper/main.tex`](paper/main.tex) (especially **§2.2 场景化产品提案**) so the report matches the code.

## Must sync

| Code change | Paper section |
|-------------|---------------|
| Audio backend (Godot API, commands, fallback, placeholder default) | §2.2 音频后端与 Godot API 集成, 表 `tab:godot-api` |
| Five-subsystem architecture | §2.2 系统架构与方法论 |
| Focus formula / symbols | §2.2 表 `tab:acs-vars`, 式 \eqref{eq:focus-raw}, \eqref{eq:focus-ema} |
| Transition timings ($T_d$, $T_c$, $\tau_f$, $\tau_r$, $\varepsilon$) | §2.2 + 有效性分析 |
| Config keys in `config/default.yaml` | §2.2 配置项（`backend`, `prefer_mp3`, `fallback_to_placeholder` 等） |
| Privacy model | §2.2 隐私与本地部署 |

## Terminology

- Use **Godot Engine** (optional sidecar + TCP JSON) or **PlaceholderMixer** (default, sounddevice).
- Describe **four-layer stems** (ambient / rhythm / harmonic / accent) when using Godot; flat main+pad assets otherwise.
- Python host + optional Godot audio sidecar; default playback is in-process via PlaceholderMixer.

## Do not sync

- Part 1 literature review unless citations change.
- Hypothetical user-study numbers in 有效性分析 unless the user asks to revise them.
